cars %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = speed) +
  aes(y = dist) +
  geom_point(alpha = .6,
             color = "navy",
             size = 5) +
  annotate(geom = "text",
           x = 3,
           y = 110, 
           label = "Data from Ezekiel's classic\n'Methods of Correlation Analysis.'", 
           color = "navy",
           family = "Times", 
           hjust = 0,
           lineheight = .8) +
  labs(y = "Stopping distance (ft)") +
  labs(x = "Speed (mph)") +
  ggthemes::theme_solarized(base_family = "Times")

iris %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = Sepal.Length) +
  aes(y = Sepal.Width) +
  geom_point() +
  aes(color = Species) +
  facet_wrap(~Species) +
  labs(color = NULL) +
  labs(x = "Sepal length") +
  labs(y = "Sepal width") +
  labs(title = "Sepal Width v. Sepal Length for \ndifferent Secies of Irises") +
  labs(tag = "Plot 1") +
  theme_minimal() +
  ggeasy::easy_remove_legend()

gapminder::gapminder %>% 
  filter(continent == "Oceania") %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = year) +
  aes(y = lifeExp) +
  geom_line() +
  aes(linetype = country) +
  labs(y = "Life Expectancy") +
  labs(linetype = NULL) +
  labs(x = NULL) +
  ggthemes::theme_fivethirtyeight()

gapminder::gapminder %>% 
  filter(year == 2002) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = lifeExp) +
  geom_histogram(alpha = .7) +
  geom_rug() +
  aes(fill = continent) +
  aes(color = continent) +
  scale_color_viridis_d() +
  scale_fill_viridis_d() +
  facet_wrap(~continent) +
  ggthemes::theme_tufte() +
  ggeasy::easy_remove_legend() +
  labs(x = "Life Expectancy") +
  labs(title = "Distribution of life expectancies by continent")

gapminder::gapminder %>% 
  filter(year == 2002) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = lifeExp) +
  aes(y = continent) +
  geom_boxplot(alpha = .7) +
  geom_jitter(height = .2) +
  aes(fill = continent) +
  aes(color = continent) +
  labs(title = "Distribution of life expectancies by continent") +  
  ggthemes::theme_pander() +
  ggeasy::easy_remove_legend()

gapminder::gapminder %>% 
  filter(year == 2002) %>% 
  arrange(-gdpPercap) %>% 
  slice(1:10) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(y = country) +
  aes(x = gdpPercap) +
  geom_col(alpha = .8) + 
  aes(y = reorder(country, gdpPercap)) +
  aes(fill = country == "United States") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("darkgrey", "steelblue")) +
  labs(x = "GDP per Capita ($US)") +
  labs(y = NULL) +
  labs(title = "Top 10 Countries in GDP per Capita in 2002") +
  ggthemes::theme_few() +
  ggeasy::easy_remove_legend() +
  annotate(geom = "text",
           x = 40000, 
           y = 5,
           label = "The US has one of\nthe highest per capita\nGDPs in the world",
           color = "steelblue") +
  annotate(geom = "curve",
           x = 40000,
           y = 6.5,
           xend = 40000,
           yend = 9, 
           curvature = .25)

readr::read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2020/2020-03-03/game_goals.csv') ->
game_goals
library(paletteer)
game_goals %>% 
  group_by(season) %>% 
  count() %>% 
  rename(number_of_goals = n) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = season) +
  aes(y = number_of_goals) +
  geom_col() +
  aes(fill = season) +
  scale_fill_paletteer_c("gameofthrones::jon_snow") + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_line() +
  geom_area(alpha = .2,
            fill = "magenta") +
  geom_segment(aes(xend = season,
                   yend = number_of_goals)) +
  ggthemes::theme_foundation() +
  ggeasy::easy_remove_legend()

readr::read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2020/2020-03-17/office_ratings.csv') ->
  office_ratings
office_ratings %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(y = as_factor(season)) +
  aes(y = fct_rev(as_factor(season))) +
  aes(x = imdb_rating) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  geom_jitter(height = .1)

office_ratings %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = air_date) +
  aes(y = imdb_rating) +
  geom_point() + 
  aes(color = episode) +
  scale_color_viridis_c() +
  geom_smooth() + 
  annotate(geom = "text",
           x = as.Date("2007-01-01"),
           y = 7,
           label = "'The Office' has\nseen highs and lows\n in ratings")
